Is it ready? It's all right. Otherwise don't cook.

14:36.600 --> 14:37.720
It's so much ready Mother.

14:37.920 --> 14:41.720
Otherwise I can come back and have. I'm not in a hurry, at all.

14:46.320 --> 14:54.080
So you have to little bit educate Me about America.

14:54.680 --> 14:56.400
How to tackle them really.

14:59.120 --> 15:02.040
I'll do everything I can. I'll do everything I can.

15:02.440 --> 15:05.200
Now you just tell Me about. Or say, take it like this,

15:05.960 --> 15:09.240
when you came to Sahaja Yoga what impressed you,

15:09.440 --> 15:13.999
how you behave you see, what was your psychological barrier? Let's see that.

15:14.360 --> 15:16.320
Because you see that's how I can tackle them.

15:18.720 --> 15:19.640
What do you say?

15:25.040 --> 15:29.440
I think it was the [intimately slope] connected with the things I did before

15:30.200 --> 15:36.040
with my preconceptions about what Realization was, wasn't, and

15:36.560 --> 15:40.920
well I had to realize what I had to fulfill. It was really...

15:43.080 --> 15:45.880
All right, all right, doesn't matter, doesn't matter. Doesn't matter.

15:46.120 --> 15:51.520
So through the [unclear], so I realized that,

15:52.160 --> 15:54.160
I couldn't compare it with anything,

15:54.360 --> 15:57.320
and I couldn't judge it with anything because it's [quite apart].

15:57.520 --> 15:59.200
Come here. Come here.

15:59.400 --> 16:02.760
It's a good idea to understand it that way.

16:03.480 --> 16:05.920
You see because Sahaja Yoga has many, many aspects

16:06.120 --> 16:07.680
and many you see things are,

16:08.040 --> 16:11.840
but to whom it will appeal what is we should try to find out, isn't it?

16:12.040 --> 16:14.920
What intellectual side of Sahaja Yoga appealed to you?

16:15.160 --> 16:17.999
Oh, I didn't rely to the things I knew.

16:18.360 --> 16:19.200
Knew already.

16:19.400 --> 16:23.160
But from experience and I could see that here must be something,

16:23.400 --> 16:26.400
by which I judge other things by that rose and judged

16:26.880 --> 16:29.080
Sahaja yoga what I did before,

16:29.320 --> 16:32.400
because nothing else has given me, that thing, thoughtless awareness.

16:33.280 --> 16:36.920
So then how shoud I proceed with them? Should I tell them that,

16:38.360 --> 16:40.960
if I tell them say for example that nothing you can relate it to,

16:41.280 --> 16:45.640
whatever you have known so far. Will they be happy to know that?

16:46.560 --> 16:49.680
That, that should be a good thing to say.

16:50.840 --> 16:54.720
I mean it appealed to me anyway but rest let's see.

16:55.080 --> 17:00.440
I mean it must because there's a little thing at least that

17:01.600 --> 17:04.040
I have to seek something new, I mean something different.

17:04.720 --> 17:07.440
The newness of it, that may appeal.

17:07.680 --> 17:08.800
Yes.

17:09.600 --> 17:13.880
The idea that I had trouble with, was the only the way to deal with

17:14.240 --> 17:17.920
cause I had all these ideas within otherwise, different.

17:18.200 --> 17:19.600
No idea should have.

17:20.600 --> 17:27.200
That sort of [napoleonesian], sophisticated and modern staff, and I think

17:27.560 --> 17:30.000
they haven't been limited to one thing,

17:30.560 --> 17:33.240
cause at first was [unclear].

17:33.440 --> 17:35.600
Accept that there's only one [way] for everyone.

17:36.280 --> 17:41.440
Tell them that seems to be a difficult thing for most people, the Nirakar.

17:43.720 --> 17:48.400
But why, the basic reason they want to have many things because

17:49.720 --> 17:55.080
see the choice, a choice, they want to have a choice.

17:55.680 --> 17:59.080
That's a very ego feeling you see,

17:59.440 --> 18:01.280
because as I told you that in America if you go,

18:01.480 --> 18:04.280
you must better ask them how to open the tap.

18:05.360 --> 18:06.520
Otherwise try to open the tap

18:06.720 --> 18:11.480
and you may find you are going into the swimming pool.

18:12.480 --> 18:15.560
And they have all different types, tiles they'll have different,

18:16.160 --> 18:17.520
the door knobs different,

18:17.720 --> 18:20.040
the opening style different, everything different.

18:20.640 --> 18:22.560
So this choice bussiness you see.

18:23.360 --> 18:28.720
But there is no choice with Divine. It's already decided.

18:30.280 --> 18:32.560
But that you find it difficult to accept like that.

18:37.400 --> 18:43.680
When it is selling, when it is selling, then you can have choice.

18:44.880 --> 18:47.560
But when somebody's giving, how can you have choice?

18:52.240 --> 18:53.880
But you can't understand giving,

18:56.520 --> 18:59.360
because that is also not related to what you have known so far.

18:59.880 --> 19:01.480
[You are merely a human being.]

19:18.840 --> 19:22.120
Still going inside.

19:22.480 --> 19:28.040
It's like the feeding of the five thousands Mother.

19:28.360 --> 19:29.640
You are hungry?

19:29.920 --> 19:30.840
Can you believe it?

19:35.080 --> 19:37.560
Believe Mother, yes, we can.

19:44.400 --> 19:45.720
Twenty one.

19:45.920 --> 19:47.040
Now, she take it. So much.

19:49.000 --> 19:52.520
Thirty-one Mother.

19:52.720 --> 19:54.040
Really?

19:54.240 --> 19:55.360
Yes.

19:56.560 --> 19:57.840
You were all wondering.

20:00.560 --> 20:04.680
Because there was a [honey in the poppy].

20:07.280 --> 20:09.720
So many things happen like that, little, little things you see.

20:09.920 --> 20:12.160
We had this Sahasrara program.

20:12.480 --> 20:15.400
And for that they decided a very far-fetched thing.

20:15.960 --> 20:19.320
It was to go to an absolute wild place,

20:20.320 --> 20:22.840
which you are going to have this time when you will go to India.

20:23.560 --> 20:26.760
And we had to go through a, ply through a,

20:27.120 --> 20:36.440
about hundred yards of sea to go to the other side of an island.

20:36.760 --> 20:39.800
And there is open sea the other side. So we went down.

20:40.520 --> 20:46.000
And they said they have to do the cooking. So what should we do?

20:46.720 --> 20:48.960
So the boys you see, in India, are hopeless absolutely,

20:49.160 --> 20:51.320
they don't know how to do anything whatsoever.

20:52.880 --> 20:56.280
Moody and her brother, and Mr. Pradhan and all these people,

20:56.480 --> 21:00.600
they said, "Now tell us how to do this, something cooking, simple",

21:01.560 --> 21:05.800
acchha, some sort of a pulao, rice pulao. I said, "All right."

21:06.120 --> 21:09.999
While we were driving in the car you see, I told them how to do it.

21:10.640 --> 21:12.920
I told them "Take now. For how many people?"

21:13.600 --> 21:17.320
It was for, they said about three hundred people.

21:17.600 --> 21:20.400
Theree hundred people? Now you have never touched it,

21:20.600 --> 21:24.320
you don't know how to cook. They said, "Then we tell somebody."

21:24.680 --> 21:29.680
There's a cook coming out. So in the car I told them for,

21:32.440 --> 21:37.280
for three hundred people, how much rice, how much ghee,

21:37.680 --> 21:41.760
how much masala, how much everything, all that I told them in weight.

21:42.960 --> 21:45.400
In fifteen minutes I told them how to make it, everything.

21:46.520 --> 21:49.760
And, then, when we went there,

21:50.160 --> 21:54.400
it was such a perfect pulao, you can't imagine. Such a miracle.

21:55.080 --> 21:57.360
And everybody said, "We have never eaten such a pulao.

21:57.560 --> 22:00.880
Who has made this and how it has worked out?"

22:01.080 --> 22:03.040
"The cook had never done it that way", they said.

22:03.520 --> 22:07.560
And there were ten hings to be put and at least

22:08.280 --> 22:12.680
six, seven masalas to be put. This has to go there and so many things.

22:12.880 --> 22:16.200
Not like kichri. That is called like Ravan bhat, means the,

22:16.400 --> 22:21.320
as Ravana had ten heads, you see like that, it was the rice.

22:21.600 --> 22:26.160
It came out so perfect and so tasty and so fragrant,

22:27.480 --> 22:30.640
Of, I don't know, it was such a miracle for three hundred people.

22:30.840 --> 22:32.280
And they were four hundred.

22:34.280 --> 22:39.200
And the whole, I mean the masala has to be absoutely perfect for that size.

22:39.640 --> 22:41.960
And what they did, they went to the market, they all asked,

22:42.160 --> 22:45.680
"Give us so much, so much, so much, so many kilos, so many kilos", all right.

22:45.880 --> 22:48.999
And they gave it to the cook. See, this is the recipe, just try.

22:49.360 --> 22:52.920
The whole thing worked out absolutely perfect.

22:54.240 --> 22:59.080
And everybody ate and ate and ate and ate.

22:59.920 --> 23:02.120
So much so that they couldn't lift their bodies.

23:05.920 --> 23:09.120
Absolutely dead time. And I told them that returning time,

23:09.320 --> 23:10.920
better keep it six o'clock,

23:11.120 --> 23:13.560
because I know what will happen after they eat that rice.

23:14.760 --> 23:18.680
And it was absolutely sufficient for everyone.

23:20.160 --> 23:23.520
And we had taken one gentleman with us who had never been to Sahaja Yoga.

23:23.720 --> 23:26.680
He said, "I've never enjoied in my life so much, so much I enjoied now."

23:28.360 --> 23:31.240
And everything was first class and I told them about,

23:31.680 --> 23:33.840
they've made also curry out of the yogurt.

23:34.680 --> 23:36.600
"Little thing", I said, "you add to that,

23:37.680 --> 23:44.160
of the we did, called raw coconut.

23:44.920 --> 23:46.920
And the whole thing was so good

23:47.600 --> 23:50.640
